  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ensuring research quality and people&apos;s voice</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Research quality in Oxfam can benefit from overall improvement. In particular, getting better at listening to people&apos;s voices is essential.  Using an innovative method &#x2013; SenseMaker, Oxfam can create a platform to listen to people&apos;s voices about their lives and needs. This method is being applied in two cases, Iraq and Central African Republic (CAR), to hear how displaced people are managing to still have agency. A software license is needed to analyse the data. This license can be used for other initiatives of Oxfam that seek to prioritise citizen voice, and is part of OGB&apos;s overall contribution to strengthening the organisation&apos;s research quality.</narrative>
  </description>
